    help_body_html:    '<h2 style="margin-top:0">📐 Ventilation Calculation Methodology</h2><p class="muted">Physics-based model: Qmin = max(CO₂, moisture) | Qmax = heat balance. All in SI units.</p><h3>1 — Qmin: CO₂ balance (CIGR 1984)</h3><p>Temperature-independent biological minimum. Removes CO₂ produced by bird metabolism.</p><div class="info-block" style="font-family:monospace;line-height:1.9">H_total = 10.62 × W^0.75 × N_eff   [W]<br>Q_CO₂ = H_total × 0.153 / 2.6 × 1.5   [m³/h]<br><span class="muted">W=body weight [kg] · N_eff=effective flock · 0.153=CO₂ yield · 2.6‰=limit · 1.5=safety</span></div><h3>2 — Qmin: Moisture balance</h3><p>Removes water vapour from birds and open-flame heaters.</p><div class="info-block" style="font-family:monospace;line-height:1.9">Q_RH = G_total / (ρ_in × ΔW)   [m³/h]<br>G_birds = 3.72×W^0.75 × 3600/2430 × N_eff   [g/h]<br>G_heater = V_gas × 1607   [g/h]   (open flame only)<br>ΔW = W_inside_max − W_outside   [g/kg dry air]<br>W = 622·Pv/(101325−Pv)   Psat = 611.2·exp(17.67·T/(T+243.5)) Pa</div><h3>3 — Qmin final</h3><div class="info-block" style="font-family:monospace">Q_min = max(Q_CO₂, Q_RH)</div><h3>4 — Qmax: Heat balance</h3><p>Air volume that removes all bird heat via enthalpy difference ρ·Cp·ΔT.</p><div class="info-block" style="font-family:monospace;line-height:1.9">Q_max = (H_total − UA×ΔT) × 3600 / (ρ × Cp × ΔT)   [m³/h]<br>UA = building heat loss coefficient [W/°C]  (from calibration test)<br>ΔT = T_in − T_out   ρ = 353.05/(T_out+273.15) kg/m³   Cp = 1006 J/(kg·K)<br><span class="muted">Cold: UA×ΔT &gt; 0 → walls assist cooling → Qmax ↓.   Hot: UA×ΔT &lt; 0 → walls add load → Qmax ↑.</span></div><h3>5 — Heater duty cycle</h3><p>Q_vent_heat (preheating incoming ventilation air) dominates in cold weather.</p><div class="info-block" style="font-family:monospace;line-height:1.9">Q_vent_heat = (Q_min/3600) × ρ_inlet × 1006 × ΔT   [W]<br>Q_sensible_birds = 6.90 × W^0.75 × N_eff   [W]<br>duty = max(0, UA×ΔT + Q_vent_heat − Q_sensible_birds) / P_heater</div><h3>6 — Open-flame heater: CO₂ dilution</h3><div class="info-block" style="font-family:monospace;line-height:1.9">V_gas = (P_kW / 10) × duty_cycle   [m³/h natural gas]<br>CO₂_prod = V_gas × 1000   [L/h]<br>Q_dilution = (CO₂_prod / 2.6) × 1.5   [m³/h added to Qmin]<br><span class="muted">1 m³ gas → 1000 L CO₂ → 577 m³ air to dilute to 2.6‰  (≈40× combustion air)</span></div><h3>7 — Tunnel mode</h3><div class="info-block" style="font-family:monospace;line-height:1.9">Active when: age ≥ tunnel_min_day  AND  T_outside ≥ tunnel_min_temp °C<br>In tunnel mode: Q_max = q_max_base × N_eff  (full system capacity)<br>Qmin is unchanged — biological minimum always applies</div><h3>8 — Mortality correction</h3><div class="info-block" style="font-family:monospace;line-height:1.9">daily_m = 1 − (1 − total_mortality)^(1/cycle_days)<br>N_eff = N × (1 − daily_m)^(age − 1)</div><h3>9 — Evaporative Cooling (Pad &amp; Fan)</h3><p>Air is cooled by evaporating water in a cellulose pad. The thermodynamic limit is the wet-bulb temperature T_wb — determined solely by outdoor air conditions, not water temperature.</p><div class="info-block" style="font-family:monospace;line-height:1.9">T_wb (Stull 2011, ±0.3°C):<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;= T·atan(0.151977·√(RH+8.314)) + atan(T+RH) − atan(RH−1.676)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;+ 0.003918·RH^1.5·atan(0.02310·RH) − 4.686   [°C]<br>T_pad = T_db − η × (T_db − T_wb)   [°C]<br><span class="muted">η=73% @ 100 mm (225 FPM · 1.14 m/s) | η=75% @ 150 mm (350 FPM · 1.78 m/s) — calibrated vs UGA Excel 2014</span></div><h3>9.1 — Air velocity through pad</h3><div class="info-block" style="font-family:monospace;line-height:1.9">A_pad = pad_length × pad_height   [m²]<br>v = Q_fan / (A_pad × 3600)   [m/s]<br><span class="muted">100 mm: 0.60–1.75 m/s (rec 1.14) | 150 mm: 0.80–2.00 m/s (rec 1.78)<br>Too high → water droplets carried into house | Too low → mould risk</span></div><h3>9.2 — Water consumption (psychrometric mass balance)</h3><div class="info-block" style="font-family:monospace;line-height:1.9">W = 0.622 × Pv / (101325 − Pv)   [kg/kg dry air]<br>Pv = (RH/100) × 611.2 × exp(17.67T / (T+243.5))   [Pa]<br>ΔW = η × (W_sat(T_wb) − W_outside)   [kg/kg]<br>Q_water = (Q_fan/3600) × ρ × ΔW × 60   [L/min]<br><span class="muted">Accuracy ±2% vs UGA Excel (vs ±21% with simple heat balance)</span></div><h3>9.3 — Well water effect (non-adiabatic correction)</h3><p>Standard UGA model: adiabatic process, recirculated water reaches T_wb equilibrium — water temperature has no effect. With a <strong>fresh cold well supply</strong>, water absorbs extra sensible heat from the air before evaporating:</p><div class="info-block" style="font-family:monospace;line-height:1.9">ΔT_air = (ṁ_evap × Cp_water × (T_wb − T_water)) / (ṁ_air × Cp_air)   [°C]<br>T_pad_corrected = T_pad − ΔT_air<br><span class="muted">Cp_water=4186 J/(kg·°C) · Cp_air=1005 J/(kg·°C) · ρ_air=1.184 kg/m³<br>Conservative: uses evaporated flow only. Actual may be 3–5× with high pump rate.<br>Well 10°C, T_wb=23°C: effect ≈ +0.15–0.45°C | Tank &gt;T_wb: negative (reduces efficiency)</span></div><hr class="section-divider"><p class="muted" style="font-size:12px">References: CIGR (1984) · Aviagen Broiler Management Guide (2019) · Magnus formula (1844) · ASHRAE Fundamentals · UGA Evaporative Cooling Design Spreadsheet (2014)</p>',

